surance, draw\nnecessary deeds, make settle\nments and advise in all mat\nters affecting Real Estate\nWITHOUT COST to you.\nPald-ln Capital and Surplus. $27,900.\n1416 F Street.\nW. J. NEWTON. President.\nK. M. GILLETT, Treasurer.\nno30 00t\n\nFINANCIAL.\nFINANCIAL.\nii??imK?miiiiiiiiniiriiM??iin?iiiMiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiimn?miiiiiiiwiiiiiiiiuimw4>\nCapital and Profits Over $1,425,000.\n?tart the New Year.\nBy Openirag\nA Bank Account\n?in the oldest Savings Depository\n?in the District of Columbia.\nHIS is a day of good resolutions. Why not resolve\nto start the new year by opening a bank account?\nLay the foundation of financial independence\nNOW by making a deposit in our banking depart\nment. The initial deposit need not be large?any amount\nfrom ten cents up will start an account here.\nRemember, this is the oldest established savings de\npository in the District of Columbia.\nSame rate of interest paid on both large and small ac\ncounts.\nThis institution is a legal depository for court and\ntrust funds. Trusts of every character executed in the\nmost satisfactory manner.\nSafe Deposit Boxes Rented, $5 Yr.\nOFFICERS:\nTHOMAS n. JONES. President.\nE. FRANCIS RICKiS. Vice President.\nWM. D. HOOVER. Jd Vice President\nand Trust Officer.\nGEORGE HOWARD. Trea?ur?r.\nCHARLES E. NTMAN. Secretary.\nFRANK W. STONE, Asst. Treasurer.\nDIRECTORS:\nWOODBURY BI.AIR\nS. THOMAS BROWN\nWILLIAM A. H. CHURCH\nWALTER C. CLEPHANE\nWILLIAM V. COX\nWILLIAM E. EDMONSTON\nGEORGE W. GRAY\nSAMUEL B. HOLABIRD\nWILLIAM D. HOOVER\nHORACE\nTHOMAS R. JONES\nVICTOR KAI FTMANN\nSAMUEL MADDOX\nMARTIN F. MORRIS\nHENRY ORTH\nWILLIAM F. QUICRSALt.\nE. FRANCIS RIGGS\nHENRY A. WILLARD\nJOHN L. WEAVER\nWYLIE f\n\ni\n\nNational Savings\nTrost Company,\nCor. 15th St. and N. Y. Avenue.\nForty-first Year.\nELDRIDGE E. JORDAN*, BERT T. AMOS.\nPresident. Ttwwtf.\n.WALTER HIESTON, WM. T. MEREDITH,\nVice President.\nJORDAN CO., Inc.,\nReal Estate, Loans, Insurance Underwriters,\n1305 G Street N.W.\nTelephone Main 177T.\nREAL ESTATE, SALES AND LOANS. 1\nWe sell and exchange real estate in all sections of the Districted\nColumbia. We handle all that comes to us, high-priced or low\npriced, and all property placed in our hands is liberally advertised\nwithout charge to our clients.\nWe negotiate loans on real estate, and in all cases the cbaractec\nof the security is carefully inquired into.\nFIRE, LIFE AND ACCIDENT INSURANCE, i\nBeing agents for several large'companies. we are prepared to of\nfer our clients the very best facilities for placing their insurance\neither in a local or outside company, as they may prefer, at the\ncheapest current rates.\nWe insure all kinds of stocks, furniture, hawses, etc., and the.\nplacing of large lines of insurance is a specialty.\nBUILDING BRANCH.\nWe are prepared to erect houses for clients at a comparatively\nsmall advance above actual cost. This plan enables the purchaser to\narrange the house to suit his own taste.\n\"INVESTMENTS.\"\nWe can offer real estate notes varying in size from $500-to\n$50,000, netting the purchaser 5 to 6 per cent.\nWe will also purchase for our clients any local bonds or stocks,,\nalways using every effort to securc for them the very best invest\nment possible, with thorough investigation on our part.\nJORDAN CO.. Inc..\nBy Walter Hieston, Vice Pre9. 1\nj?i-'?t\nEstablished October 19, 1904.\nTh? Commercial\nNational\nCapita! $500,<1\nSurplus and Undivided Profits 231,875.07\nOfficers:\nFrederick C. Stevens.. .Pres.\nR. A. Chester, .ist Vice Pres.\nN. H. Shea... .2d Vice Pres.\nGeo. W. White Cashier\nV. B. Deyber Secretary\nDirectors:\nr. J. Brennan\nWmlter A. Brnwn\nJames A. Cablll\nRobt. A. Chester\nMrer Cohen\nWm. A. U. Church\nSnmuel <3. Cormrell\nM. J. Colbert\nH. Bradler Davidson\nJ. J. Darlington\n1 Vlitur B. Deyber\nGeo. W.\nNorman Gait\nWm. V. Ham\nRndolpb Ksuffmana\nKalpb W. Lee\nArthur 0. MoHl\nWm. A. Mearna\nJohn L. Newbold\nClarence B. ltbeem\nFrederick C. Sterena\nN. H. Sbea\nCharles F. Schneid